<ns64:section xmlns:ns64="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.documenting.examples.interpharm.architecture.drivers.drivers">
  <ns65:title xmlns:ns65="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Architectural drivers</ns65:title>
  <ns66:para xmlns:ns66="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    In this section we discuss the quality requirements prosed by business.
  </ns66:para>
  
  <ns67:section xmlns:ns67="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns68:title xmlns:ns68="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Availability and reliability</ns68:title>
    <ns69:para xmlns:ns69="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      365x24x7 availability and reliability are critical. It should be possible to perform most
      maintenance with affecting availability and without major impact on performance.
    </ns69:para>
  </ns67:section>
  
  <ns70:section xmlns:ns70="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns71:title xmlns:ns71="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Scaleability</ns71:title>
    <ns72:para xmlns:ns72="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The system must be able to comfortably process 60 claims per second.  The architecture should
      cater for future increases in load. 
    </ns72:para>
  </ns70:section>
  
  <ns73:section xmlns:ns73="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns74:title xmlns:ns74="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Maintainability</ns74:title>
    <ns75:para xmlns:ns75="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The architecture should facilitate maintainability by
      <ns76:itemizedlist xmlns:ns76="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns77:listitem xmlns:ns77="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns78:para xmlns:ns78="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          minimizing complexity,
        </ns78:para></ns77:listitem>
        <ns79:listitem xmlns:ns79="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns80:para xmlns:ns80="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          using standard technologies for which it is easy to source developer resources which can
          become quickly able to maintain the system,
        </ns80:para></ns79:listitem>
        <ns81:listitem xmlns:ns81="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns82:para xmlns:ns82="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          minimizing the code bulk,
        </ns82:para></ns81:listitem>
        <ns83:listitem xmlns:ns83="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns84:para xmlns:ns84="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          supporting maintenance on the life system, and
        </ns84:para></ns83:listitem>
        <ns85:listitem xmlns:ns85="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns86:para xmlns:ns86="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          specifying clean responsibility allocations.
        </ns86:para></ns85:listitem>
      </ns76:itemizedlist>
    </ns75:para>
  </ns73:section>
  
  <ns87:section xmlns:ns87="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns88:title xmlns:ns88="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Performance</ns88:title>
    <ns89:para xmlns:ns89="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
       The round-trip processing from receiving a claim to dispatching the response to the pharmacy
       must be below two seconds and should preferably be sub-second.
    </ns89:para>
  </ns87:section>
  
  
  <ns90:section xmlns:ns90="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns91:title xmlns:ns91="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Auditability</ns91:title>
    <ns92:para xmlns:ns92="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      All  messages received from or sent to a third party need to be logged.
    </ns92:para>
  </ns90:section>
  
  <ns93:section xmlns:ns93="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns94:title xmlns:ns94="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Monitorability</ns94:title>
    <ns95:para xmlns:ns95="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The system load and state of all components of the architecture should be monitorable.
    </ns95:para>
  </ns93:section>
  
  <ns96:section xmlns:ns96="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns97:title xmlns:ns97="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Integrability</ns97:title>
    <ns98:para xmlns:ns98="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      It should be straight forward to integrate with other medical aid administrators using their
      specific protocols. In future the system should support processing claims from different
      pharmacy systems using standard web-services based protocols.
    </ns98:para>
    
  </ns96:section>
</ns64:section>